# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project Zenith — backend environment template.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in the values:   cp .env.example .env
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# HTTP port the API gateway listens on. Optional (defaults to 8000).
PORT=8000

# ── Required for full real-data functionality ────────────────────────────────

# N2YO satellite tracking API key — used for real ISS pass times / elevations
# (/api/n2yo and the ISS visibility window inside /api/report).
# Free key: https://www.n2yo.com/api/  (register -> Profile -> API)
# Without it: the report/ISS still shows REAL position/altitude/velocity, but the
# "next pass" window/event is omitted.
N2YO_API_KEY=

# Google Gemini API key — used for the AI Sky Narrator (/api/ai and the narration
# field of /api/report).
# Free key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Without it: narration gracefully falls back to a templated summary built from
# the same REAL numbers (score, clouds, moon, ISS, brightest planet).
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ── No key required (keyless public APIs already wired) ───────────────────────
# The following data sources need NO credentials and work out of the box:
#   • NASA JPL Horizons      — planetary ephemerides / magnitudes
#   • Open-Meteo             — cloud cover + visibility (weather)
#   • Open-Meteo Geocoding   — location search (/api/location/search)
#   • Open Notify            — live ISS lat/lng
#   • CelesTrak              — ISS TLE (drives satellite.js propagation)
#   • USNO                   — moon illumination
#   • BigDataCloud           — reverse geocoding (/api/location/:lat/:lng)
#
# ── Optional / future ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AstronomyAPI (planet visibility + constellations) is NOT yet integrated.
# If/when added it needs an application id + secret (HTTP Basic):
# ASTRONOMYAPI_APP_ID=
# ASTRONOMYAPI_APP_SECRET=
